subSubSection.paragraph:
Easily confused with
G. corniculigerum
Enderlein, 1913; differs mainly by the shape of the head in dorsal view (nearly parallel-sided behind eyes in female and distinctly contracted in
G. corniculigerum
), the sculpture of the middle lobe of the mesoscutum (without fine transverse elements anteriorly; present in
G. corniculigerum
), the anteriorly more slender propleuron and the shorter pale part of the ovipositor sheath (1.0-2.1 x versus 2.8-3.5 x as long as hind basitarsus in
G. corniculigerum
).
